newsitem.title: HONG KONG: China bought 50,000T U.S. soymeal at $307 C&F.
newsitem.headline: China bought 50,000T U.S. soymeal at $307 C&F.

text.p: China bought at least one 50,000-tonne cargo of U.S. soymeal last week, for about US$307 a tonne C&F China, Chinese and Hong Kong-based trade sources said on Monday.

Chicago Board of Trade soymeal futures closed higher on Friday, fuelled partly by rumours that China purchased 50,000 tonnes of U.S. soymeal overnight on Wednesday and another 50,000 tonnes overnight on Thursday.
Sale of the second 50,000-tonne soymeal cargo could not be confirmed.
Two 10,000-tonne cargoes of Indian new-crop soymeal were heard sold to China last week at about $308 C&F China, for December delivery, industry sources said.
"Those are very aggressive prices," one oilseeds trader said, adding "There are a lot of inquiries. Everybody knows China needs meal."
